For the current development, the user can 
see: https://github.com/dmpe/rbitly

###
September 2015 - Smaller tweaks, which do not impact any functionality of the core RBitly
               - Bring up-to-date with R releases
               - Added (a very) experimental support of Ow.ly (owned by Hootsuite.com). Please (!) report bugs to 
                 the maintainer (see above).
               - Added a (less experimental) support of goo.gl (owned by Google.com). 
           
July 2015 - Initial CRAN Release.
          - Majority of methods are implemented and ready to use.
